<details><summary><div class="aug-float">▼ Augments</div> </summary>

<div class="aug-text"> 
<b>Morning Glory</b></br>
While its wielder is in MP Recharge or afflicted by Silence, Larceny's basic attacks calculate damage using MAG instead of STR and deal light-element damage.</p>

<b>Evening Primrose</b></br>
After successfully inflicting a status ailment, Grand Larceny's wielder may make a basic attack as a free action on their next turn using this weapon. This attack benefits from the Morning Glory augment, even when not in MP Recharge, and gains a bonus to its accuracy roll equal to the number of status ailments afflicting the target.</p>

<b>Nightshade (Ultimate)</b></br>
Grand Larceny's critical hits inflict Hex [sv, 5]. If that target is already Hexed, Grand Larceny may immediately trigger Hex's damage roll and restore an amount of its wielder's MP equal to half the damage inflicted. No more than 10% of the wielder's maximum MP can be restored this way per turn. </div></details>

